                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15976025" author="kenn" created="Thu, 20 Apr 2017 03:59:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If this is the case, and is not fixable quickly, we can add static validation of a graph to reject such timers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15986797" author="thw" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2017 15:15:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kenn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kenn&quot;&gt;kenn&lt;/a&gt; Instant.now() should be replaced with code that derives the processing time from the Apex streaming window ID. I can make that change. Where are the processing time timers treated as event time? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15986808" author="kenn" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2017 15:17:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I commented on your timer internals PR. I think what I mean is something different. Processing time timers should not be related to windows or watermarks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15988702" author="aljoscha" created="Fri, 28 Apr 2017 11:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Kenn is probably talking about this method: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/3e243881fe767cf30869abf5c745c26f96d66fc4/runners/apex/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/apex/translation/operators/ApexGroupByKeyOperator.java#L258-L258&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/3e243881fe767cf30869abf5c745c26f96d66fc4/runners/apex/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/runners/apex/translation/operators/ApexGroupByKeyOperator.java#L258-L258&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;TimerData&lt;/tt&gt; has a &lt;tt&gt;TimeDomain&lt;/tt&gt; field (that indicates processing time, event time, or synchronised processing time). The field is ignored and all timers are essentially treated as event-time timers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15989023" author="thw" created="Fri, 28 Apr 2017 15:39:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, also the processing time timers need to be decoupled from the input watermark as far as firing goes. I think this clear now. Waiting for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-1981&quot; title=&quot;Serialization error with TimerInternals in ApexGroupByKeyOperator&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-1981&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-1981&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; merge and then will take this up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
